---

## Reveal Logic

The backend is authoritative for reveal state.

A registry is revealed when:

```js
new Date() >= new Date(registry.reveal_datetime)
```

Before reveal:

- Hide giver names from the owner.
- Hide giver user IDs from owner-facing responses.
- Hide individual pledge amounts from the owner.
- Hide viewer private notes from the owner.

After reveal:

- Show giver identity.
- Show prepared item details.
- Show individual pledge details.
- Show viewer private notes.
- Enable thank-you letter creation.

Never rely on frontend-only hiding for privacy-sensitive data.

---

## Item Quantity Logic

For each item:

```txt
total_reserved = sum(quantity where status = reserved)
total_prepared = sum(quantity where status = prepared)
total_claimed = total_reserved + total_prepared
available_quantity = quantity_needed - total_claimed
```

Do not allow users to reserve or prepare more than the remaining available quantity.

Display states:

- Available
- Partially Reserved
- Reserved
- Partially Prepared
- Prepared
- Closed

---

## Category-Aware Fields

Default categories:

- Dorm / Apartment
- Tech
- Clothing
- Accessories
- School / Work Supplies
- Self-Care
- Food / Groceries
- Experience
- Cash Fund
- Custom

Use flexible item attributes for category-specific fields.

Examples:

- size
- color
- brand
- model
- material
- dimensions
- flavor
- compatibility
- preferred_date
- location

Do not hardcode every possible item field into the main item table unless it is globally useful.

---

## API Design Rules

Use REST-style API routes.

Recommended routes:

```txt
GET    /api/auth/google
GET    /api/auth/google/callback
GET    /api/auth/me
POST   /api/auth/logout

POST   /api/registries
GET    /api/registries
GET    /api/registries/:registryId
PATCH  /api/registries/:registryId
POST   /api/registries/join

POST   /api/registries/:registryId/items
PATCH  /api/items/:itemId
DELETE /api/items/:itemId
PATCH  /api/items/:itemId/reorder

POST   /api/items/:itemId/reserve
POST   /api/reservations/:reservationId/prepare
POST   /api/reservations/:reservationId/cancel

POST   /api/registries/:registryId/cash-funds
PATCH  /api/cash-funds/:fundId
DELETE /api/cash-funds/:fundId
POST   /api/cash-funds/:fundId/pledge

GET    /api/registries/:registryId/reveal

POST   /api/thank-you
GET    /api/thank-you/inbox
PATCH  /api/thank-you/:messageId/seen
```

Validate all request bodies with Zod or equivalent.

---

## Security Rules

Always enforce authorization on the backend.

Rules:

- All write actions require authentication.
- Registry edits require owner role.
- Viewer actions require registry membership.
- Reveal details require owner role and revealed state.
- Thank-you messages can only be created by the registry owner after reveal.
- Thank-you messages can only be read by the intended giver or the registry owner.
- Never expose hidden contributor information before reveal.
- Never trust user IDs from the client when session user is available.

---

## Frontend UX Rules

The app should feel premium, modern, and mobile-first.

Use social-media-inspired UX patterns without social features:

- Card-based item feeds
- Large tap targets
- Sticky headers when useful
- Bottom navigation on mobile
- Floating action button for owner actions
- Bottom sheets for quick actions
- Smooth modals
- Skeleton loading states
- Friendly empty states
- Minimal page clutter

Do not add:

- likes
- comments
- reactions
- follows
- social activity feeds
- public user profiles

---

